All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CalendarActivity
    Launches the Calender app activity to allow user to select a date and returns the date to the activity that started CalenderActivity.
    CustomIngredientArrayAdapter
    The custom array adapter for ingredients.
    CustomMealPlanArrayAdapter
    Custom array adaptor for meals that allow ListView in MealPlanActivity to display meals correctly
    CustomRecipeArrayAdapter
    Custom array adapter for Recipe class
    CustomShoppingItemArrayAdapter
    The custom array adapter for ingredients.
    ExampleInstrumentedTest
    Instrumented test, which will execute on an Android device.
    Ingredient
    Ingredient object with the description, best before date, location, count, units (for count), and category an ingredient
    IngredientActivity
    The Activity responsible for Ingredient Storage functionality, it sets up UI elements of ingredient storage, calls IngredientFragment to allow user to add/edit Ingredients, and allows movement to other activities.
    IngredientFragment
    Fragment that allows user to add/edit ingredients to ingredient storage via a adaptor design and to firebase
    IngredientFragment.OnFragmentInteractionListener  
    IngredientTest  
    Meal
    the meal class is used for display and data storage purposes since it's essentially an abstraction of ingredients and recipes.
    MealPlanActivity
    the main hub for all MealPlan related functionality.
    MealPlanFragment
    Allows user to add a new meal into MealPlan.
    MealPlanScaleFragment
    Allows user to edit scale for a meal recipe
    MealPlanScaleFragment.OnFragmentInteractionListener  
    MealPlanTest  
    Recipe
    Recipe object with the title, prep time, number of servings, comments, picture, and category of recipe
    RecipeActivity
    recipe activity responsible for all recipe functionality.
    RecipeFragment
    Fragment for Recipe which allows user to add/edit a recipe
    RecipeFragment.OnFragmentInteractionListener  
    RecipeIngredientsActivity
    Allows user to select Ingredients from Ingredient Storage and add them to a recipe.
    RecipeTest  
    ShoppingItem
    shopping item class for shoppingList functionality
    ShoppingItemFragment
    A fragment that allows user to edit shopping items or add an existing one to Ingredient storage by filling in the required values.
    ShoppingItemFragment.OnFragmentInteractionListener
    adaptor to interact with ShoppingListActivity
    ShoppingListActivity
    Main activity for all shopping list functionality.
    ShoppingListTest  
    UnitTests
